CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F327A1783691326
OL,3,CKing Charles visits Scottish Borders
OL,4,Ctown of Jedburgh
OL,6,FHe watched a procession of horses led
OL,7,Fby the Callant. The Callant is a young
OL,8,Fman chosen each year to lead the
OL,9,Fhistoric festival and represent the
OL,10,Ftown. He was accompanied by his
OL,11,Fentourage, who dismounted to perform a
OL,12,Ftraditional reel for His Majesty.
OL,14,FCallant Robbie Thomson said: "I'm not
OL,15,Fthe greatest horseman and I'm not the
OL,16,Fgreatest dancer. So I was a bit
OL,17,Fnervous but I was fine. And King was
OL,18,Freally nice to speak to.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,328,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F327A1783691326
OL,3,CKing Charles visits Scottish Borders
OL,4,Ctown of Jedburgh
OL,6,F"It's obviously unbelievable. We knew
OL,7,Fit was going to be a big event, coming
OL,8,Fup the street with the flag and
OL,9,Flooking to your left and seeing the
OL,10,FKing. It's such a good feeling."
OL,12,FThe town was last visited by a member
OL,13,Fof the Royal Family in April 2006,
OL,14,Fwhen The Princess Royal opened
OL,15,FJedforest Bandstand.
OL,17,FThe King also met with Gabrielle
OL,18,FHackney, the owner of Jedburgh
OL,19,FChocolate House. He told her he was
OL,20,Falready familiar with one of
OL,21,FJedburgh's local treats.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
